# Append-only changelog in version.md

After you finish making code changes in this project (features, fixes, refactors, config), **append** a short entry to `version.md` at the project root.

## Hard rules

- **Append only** — never delete, clear, overwrite, or rewrite existing entries in `version.md`
- Do this for **every** batch of code changes you make in a turn (not only when the user asks)
- Skip when the only change is the `version.md` entry itself
- Skip pure Q&A / read-only turns with no file edits

## Entry format

Append at the end of the file:

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM ±HH:MM — short title

- What changed (1–3 bullets: files/areas and why)
```

Use the **current local date and time** with numeric UTC offset (e.g. `2026-07-21 14:09 +05:30`). Keep it brief and factual so `version.md` is a running development log.
